originalText.text: One of my benefits through Aetna insurance is if I fill out a health assessment thru Active Health I would get  $75.00 deposited in a incentive account with Wage Works.  My wife and myself did our assessments 12/22/14 and have not received nothing yet. Last month 6/29/15 I finally got a hold of someone that did more than that there were other cases like this of people from my company that had the same issue like the previous times i called.  She filled a incident inquiry and gave me a incident number, and told me someone would respond in and couple of days. I called again on 7/6/15 and the gentlemen said the same thing that he would forward it again to technical support and someone would respond in a couple of day.  It is now 7/29/15 and I received no responses, so I called told to a supervisor, he gave me a number of technical support, so I called them and they told me that it was sent the level 2 support team earlier is morning and 8am and I would get and answer in the next couple of days.  I not going to hold my breath on that answer...

originalText.text:
I called Aetna to update my address.   I was told it was updated.   I then received mailings from Active Health to the old address.   I checked in with my Aetna Health concierge to get my address updated at Active Health.   They replied with "We have reviewed your policy and did
not find anything with Active Health that is affiliated with Aetna so it may be the reason why they do not have your correct address."   That left me quite stumped with how to proceed.   I then asked them if Active Health was a scam corporation since they don't appear to be affiliated with Active Health.   They then gave me a number to call at Active Health to get my address updated.   I called this number and spoke with Marie who after about 15 minutes of spelling and re-spelling my name, put me on hold twice, then asked for my hire date and the company I work for.  After that, she wanted my birth date and asked me to re-spell my name again.  After she couldn't get the spelling correct, I finally couldn't take this anymore and hung up.   Terribly Poor service at Aetna & Active Health.
